text:
I'm trying to design my infra for creating, storing, and retrieving embeddings in my AI applications and was wondering what are the different paths for it. I'm especially interested in NLP, but vision/multimodal could be interesting too.

Whether it's related to performance, scalability, or something else entirely, I'd love to hear your experiences and insights. Looking forward to your responses!

Show HN: CookThis, the app that fights food waste
text:
Hey HN!

I've just launched CookThis, my new app that helps fight food waste by using up leftover ingredients. It uses ML in a couple of ways to aid this, both by using a CNN to detect ingredients from a camera feed, and by using an LLM to generate new recipes.

Would be great to get some feedback! There's a week free trial available with no commitment

text: I get the sense that it's not possible to build an interesting (non-computer) physical product anymore in the US/EU without accidentally crossing into someone else's patent portfolio.  Am I wrong?

title: Ask HN: I want an app that can help me find back my memories by entering keyword
text: Do you have the same experience like me? When something come into my mind(for example, "waht is survivorship bias"), it's so familiar, but just don't know where I have read it, that feeling is too bad! I'm not a smart guy, and I don't have the ability to remember all things I have read. So, I'm want to kown if there's a tool that I can put all things in it(articles, videos, images, podcasts, etc. I don't want to manage them, just want a place to throw them in), and when I input a keyword like "meditation", it will offer me the sources I had put in. I think the difficulities is to parse the videos, images and audios instead of text files.

Ask HN: Why Microsoft sill asks security questions during the account setup?
text:
I had to reinstall one laptop and Microsoft is really pushing you towards using their on-line MS accounts. Even if manage not to create on for the local account you still get asked with three security questions.

Didn't they get the memo that this is not so good security measure? Why are they still insisting on it?
